projects.description:
INEP is the main government agency responsible for monitoring the quality of higher education in the country.

-> As an Institutional Evaluator for INEP, I have acquired skills in:

-> Analysis of indicators;

-> Preparation of analytical reports and parameterization of results;

-> Self-management skills;

-> Ability to define clear objectives and analyze business problems for performance metric measurement;

-> Time management and preparation of technical reports.

Kroton Group is the largest educational company in the country in terms of the number of students and courses offered per year, proving to be a high-performance company in the qualification of workers with higher education.

-> I developed research related to improving local quality of life;

-> I coordinated working groups for urban indicator analysis, mapping of areas with high potential for real estate production and proposal for rehabilitation of public areas;

-> Working with continuous evaluation processes, I gained experience in performance analysis and designing indicators capable of mapping deficiencies in students;

-> As a teacher and architect, I developed skills for teamwork, mediation and conflict management, more assertive processes for feedback and performance evaluation.

-> I worked with active methodologies, always focused on enabling students to work in the job market developing hard and soft skills.

-> I acquired good skills for preparing and managing teams in multidisciplinary projects due to the need for interaction between various areas of activity.

profile_positions.description:
The Polytechnic School of the University of São Paulo is one of the top ten universities in Latin America and one of the best public universities in the country. It has achieved a score of 6 on CAPES, qualifying it as a cutting-edge research institution, reflecting the rigor of the training offered to scientists.

My research aims to identify urban processes through the exploration of Big Data, considering phenomena from the past 30 years. The research involves:

-> Data Mining and Data Wrangling;
-> Construction of indicators;
-> Predictive analysis with machine learning;
-> Statistical and deterministic analysis;
-> Analysis and mapping of phenomena;
-> Geoprocessing of Urban Data with QGIS;
-> ETL processes for data cleaning, storage, and processing;
-> Programming languages R, Python, and SQL;
-> Storage in MySQL databases;
-> Business Intelligence (BI) & Business Analytics (BA) analysis for Big Data;
-> Definition and testing of hypotheses.
